    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-04T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-04T08:00:00-05:00" n="321"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.75/394: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tirana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-04T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 4, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Legation’s 13, April 3, 4 p.m. Although negotiations between the Italian and
                    Albanian Governments are continuing and have not broken down according to
                    information given to me by the Albanian Foreign Minister the situation for
                    Albania is admitted to be grave. Reports from the Greek Consul at Valona to the
                    Greek Legation are to the effect that the Italian Consul there has announced
                    that Italian troops will occupy Valona either Wednesday or Thursday of this
                    week. It is also reported that the Albanian Prefect has armed the Moslems of
                    Valona for resistance. More than 60,000 troops are camped at Bari according to
                    report brought back by our American courier. The situation is complicated for
                    the King since the Queen is hourly expecting a baby.</p>
                <p>Copy sent to Rome.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
